<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>YelpCamp</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/main.css">
    </head>
    <body>
    
    <nav class="navbar navbar-default">
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <div class="navbar-header">
                <a class="navbar-brand" href="/campgrounds">YelpCamp</a>
            </div>
            <div class="collapse navbar-collapse">
                <ul class="nav navbar-nav navbar-right">
                    <!--So we're checking if a current user variable is empty, then we're going to show these-->
                    <% if(!currentUser){ %>
                        <li><a href="/login">Log In</a></li>
                        <li><a href="/register">Sign Up</a></li>
                        <!--Otherwise we'll show the logout link.-->
                    <% } else { %>
                        <li><a href="#">Signed In As <%= currentUser.username %></a></li>
                        <li><a href="/logout">Logout</a></li>
                    <% } %>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>
    
    <div class="container">
        <!--just having error exist: if(error) : isn't enough for us to want to display error. So what we want to do is check if (error.length < 0) because even when error is empty, when there is nothing in there, it's still an empty array. And if we just check if([]), if empty array, that's not falsie. Empty array is truthy. So you want to check if error exists AND if it has an item inside of it. So if true, if there's anything in the error array, if the length is greater than zero, if(error.length > 0), then display this-->
        <% if(error && error.length > 0){ %>
            <div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert">
                <%= error %>
            </div>
        <% } %>
        
        <% if(success && success.length > 0){ %>
            <div class="alert alert-success" role="alert">
                <%= success %>
            </div>
        <% } %>
    </div>